<pb>
<milestone unit="page" n="164">
<lb>
<lb>
<lg n="45" type="stanza">
<l n="222">She&rsquo;s past the bridge that&rsquo;s in the dale, </l>
<l n="223">And now the thought torments her sore, </l>
<l n="224">Johnny perhaps his horse forsook, </l>
<l n="225">To hunt the moon that&rsquo;s in the brook, </l>
<l n="226">And never will be heard of more. </l>
</lg>
<lg n="46" type="stanza">
<l n="227">And now she&rsquo;s high upon the down, </l>
<l n="228">Alone amid a prospect wide; </l>
<l n="229">There&rsquo;s neither Johnny nor his horse, </l>
<l n="230">Among the fern or in the gorse; </l>
<l n="231">There&rsquo;s neither doctor nor his guide. </l>
</lg>
<lg n="47" type="stanza">
<l n="232">&ldquo;Oh saints! what is become of him? </l>
<l n="233">&ldquo;Perhaps he&rsquo;s climbed into an oak, </l>
<l n="234">&ldquo;Where he will stay till he is dead; </l>
<l n="235">&ldquo;Or sadly he has been misled, </l>
<l n="236">&ldquo;And joined the wandering gypsey-folk. </l>
</lg>
