<lg n="70" type="stanza">
<l n="347">I to the muses have been bound, </l>
<l n="348">These fourteen years, by strong indentures;</l>
<l n="349">Oh gentle muses! let me tell </l>
<l n="350">But half of what to him befel, </l>
<l n="351">For sure he met with strange adventures. </l>
</lg>
<lg n="71" type="stanza">
<l n="352">Oh gentle muses! is this kind? </l>
<l n="353">Why will ye thus my suit repel? </l>
<l n="354">Why of your further aid bereave me? </l>
<l n="355">And can you thus unfriended leave me? </l>
<l n="356">Ye muses! whom I love so well. </l>
</lg>
<pb>
<milestone unit="page" n="173">
<lb>
<lb>
<lg n="72" type="stanza">
<l n="357">Who&rsquo;s yon, that, near the waterfall, </l>
<l n="358">Which thunders down with headlong force,</l>
<l n="359">Beneath the moon, yet shining fair, </l>
