<pb>
<milestone unit="page" n="177">
<lb>
<lb>
<lg n="84" type="stanza">
<l n="417">The pony, Betty, and her boy, </l>
<l n="418">Wind slowly through the woody dale: </l>
<l n="419">And who is she, be-times abroad, </l>
<l n="420">That hobbles up the steep rough road? </l>
<l n="421">Who is it, but old Susan Gale? </l>
</lg>
<lg n="85" type="stanza">
<l n="422">Long Susan lay deep lost in thought, </l>
<l n="423">And many dreadful fears beset her, </l>
<l n="424">Both for her messenger and nurse; </l>
<l n="425">And as her mind grew worse and worse, </l>
<l n="426">Her body it grew better.</l>
</lg>
<lg n="86" type="stanza">
<l n="427">She turned, she toss&rsquo;d herself in bed,</l>
<l n="428">On all sides doubts and terrors met her; </l>
<l n="429">Point after point did she discuss; </l>
<l n="430">And while her mind was fighting thus, </l>
<l n="431">Her body still grew better. </l>
